                ab7aecad34d feat(sk-doc): enforce kebab catalog content by default; retire underscore contract\n* deep-review/0092-session-shipped-work  012652b479d fix(deep-loop): harden the four 007 security services (036/007)\n  integration-v2                         71e18c224c3 fix(sk-doc): complete deferred-integration reference completion on settled v4\n  main                                   9c5c7c5bde4 Merge origin/main README updates into v3.6.0.0 release\n  sk-design/0070-011-impl                0a7842a9c1c [behind 85] docs(sk-design): document the styles-library utilization capability (packet 011)\n  sk-design/0071-005-impl                0a6bca4f02d feat(sk-design): add the design-md-generator v3 schema contract (packet 011 phase 005)\n  sk-design/0072-007-impl                5099759854f feat(sk-design): add the shared corpus-context seam (packet 011 phase 007)\n  sk-design/0073-006-impl                ca0f3f21a76 feat(sk-design): add bounded STUDY exemplars for design-md-generator (packet 011 phase 006)\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git branch -v 2>&1 | head -10","time":{"start":1784606309228,"end":1784606309234}},"id":"prt_f82d33b430017dcubCXwy12HlI","sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","messageID":"msg_f82d32808001aX9MGukDFHbFKB"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606309436,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82d33ac877b38e3b6c66","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show --stat bf0986cecd 2>&1 | head -50"},"output":"commit bf0986cecd33f8cb48feb9d433fdd2e26e7b9b0f\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 19:46:31 2026 +0200\n\n    feat(sk-design): implement styles-DB evolution Phase 0 foundation (015/001)\n    \n    Lift packet 015 phase 001-foundation from a design-only spec to a built,\n    measured foundation for the sk-design styles database:\n    \n    - Generation manifest: versioned multi-artifact manifest with a single\n      fsynced pointer-flip publish, atomic rollback, and N-generation retention.\n    - Residency-honest stage telemetry: per-stage latency/throughput/RSS across\n      the indexer and query lanes, with genuine unattributed accounting\n      (elapsed minus sum-of-spans) and honest native vs JS-resident labels.\n    - Pinned differential oracle: freezes current retrieval/index output through\n      the shared canonicalizer and replays the full scenario matrix (incl. the\n      vector and cursor lanes) byte-for-byte at 1x/10x/100x, over deterministic,\n      honestly-diverse fixtures.\n    - Relevance judgments: an honestly-labeled silver/authored seed\n      (humanLabelingRequired flagged, provenance per row) - no fabricated gold.\n    \n    Built, adversarially reviewed (opus/xhigh, 5/5 findings confirmed), and the\n    two P1s fixed. Telemetry stays a pure side-channel: the retrieval DTO is\n    byte-identical with and without it, so the oracle golden is unchanged.\n    \n    Verified: 69/69 styles/_db tests + 20/20 _engine tests green;\n    validate.sh --strict on 015/001-foundation = 0 errors, 0 warnings.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PqyZVWPMuG8aTNsmVnj35K\n\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md    |  53 +++-\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/fixtures.test.mjs         |  74 +++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/index.mjs       |   5 +\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/judgments.test.mjs        | 104 +++++++\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/manifest.test.mjs         | 239 ++++++++++++++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs | 157 +++++++++++\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/telemetry.test.mjs        | 234 ++++++++++++++++\n .../skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs      |  70 +++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs   | 308 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs  | 105 ++++---\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs |  33 +++\n .../styles/_db/oracle/differential-oracle.mjs      | 167 +++++++++++\n .../golden/degraded-disable-fts.canonical.json     |   1 +\n .../_db/oracle/golden/exact-reuse.canonical.json   |   1 +\n .../_db/oracle/golden/exclusions.canonical.json    |   1 +\n .../_db/oracle/golden/facet-filter.canonical.json  |   1 +\n .../_db/oracle/golden/fts-text.canonical.json      |   1 +\n .../styles/_db/oracle/golden/hybrid.canonical.json |   1 +\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/oracle/golden/index.json  |  41 +++\n","metadata":{"output":"commit bf0986cecd33f8cb48feb9d433fdd2e26e7b9b0f\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 19:46:31 2026 +0200\n\n    feat(sk-design): implement styles-DB evolution Phase 0 foundation (015/001)\n    \n    Lift packet 015 phase 001-foundation from a design-only spec to a built,\n    measured foundation for the sk-design styles database:\n    \n    - Generation manifest: versioned multi-artifact manifest with a single\n      fsynced pointer-flip publish, atomic rollback, and N-generation retention.\n    - Residency-honest stage telemetry: per-stage latency/throughput/RSS across\n      the indexer and query lanes, with genuine unattributed accounting\n      (elapsed minus sum-of-spans) and honest native vs JS-resident labels.\n    - Pinned differential oracle: freezes current retrieval/index output through\n      the shared canonicalizer and replays the full scenario matrix (incl. the\n      vector and cursor lanes) byte-for-byte at 1x/10x/100x, over deterministic,\n      honestly-diverse fixtures.\n    - Relevance judgments: an honestly-labeled silver/authored seed\n      (humanLabelingRequired flagged, provenance per row) - no fabricated gold.\n    \n    Built, adversarially reviewed (opus/xhigh, 5/5 findings confirmed), and the\n    two P1s fixed. Telemetry stays a pure side-channel: the retrieval DTO is\n    byte-identical with and without it, so the oracle golden is unchanged.\n    \n    Verified: 69/69 styles/_db tests + 20/20 _engine tests green;\n    validate.sh --strict on 015/001-foundation = 0 errors, 0 warnings.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PqyZVWPMuG8aTNsmVnj35K\n\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/README.md    |  53 +++-\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/fixtures.test.mjs         |  74 +++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/index.mjs       |   5 +\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/judgments.test.mjs        | 104 +++++++\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/manifest.test.mjs         | 239 ++++++++++++++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/__tests__/oracle.test.mjs | 157 +++++++++++\n .../styles/_db/__tests__/telemetry.test.mjs        | 234 ++++++++++++++++\n .../skills/sk-design/styles/_db/canonical.mjs      |  70 +++++\n .../sk-design/styles/_db/generation-manifest.mjs   | 308 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/indexer.mjs  | 105 ++++---\n .opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_db/operator.mjs |  33 +++\n .../styles/_db/oracle/differential-oracle.mjs      | 167 +++++++