{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606557618,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82d6fb787af29be27769","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && grep -rn \"/design:\\|commands/design\" .opencode/skills/sk-design/ 2>&1 | grep -v -E \"node_modules|\\.git/\" | head -30"},"output":".opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:201:`/interface:{design,foundations,motion,audit,design-reference}` maps to the unchanged `interface`, `foundations`, `motion`, `audit` and `md-generator` mode IDs. All five commands reference one shared nine-stage creation contract. The corresponding `/design:*` commands remain thin compatibility aliases.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:3:description: \"Five canonical /interface:* creation commands, one shared nine-stage contract, and additive /design:* compatibility aliases.\"\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:20:The former `/design:{interface,foundations,motion,audit,md-generator}` commands remain thin compatibility aliases. The aliases are additive and preserve arguments while executing the canonical contracts in place.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:30:Compatibility metadata maps each `/design:*` alias one-to-one to a canonical `/interface:*` command. The alias layer does not create new modes, remove old consumers or change the stable mode roster.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:43:| `.opencode/commands/design/*.md` | Compatibility routers | Preserves the five `/design:*` aliases. |\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:26:- `/design:interface`, `/design:foundations`, `/design:motion`, `/design:audit` and `/design:md-generator` remain thin compatibility aliases.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:8:> Covers the net cumulative change since v1.2.0.0's mode-local procedure operating model: the five `/design:*` commands moved to a router+assets shape, a sixth transport mode joined the registry, and the first-ever full manual execution of the playbook found and fixed a real routing/authoring-boundary defect for every mode.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:15:- Router+assets command shape for all five `/design:*` commands, mirroring the `speckit`/`create`/`deep` command family pattern: a thin router file plus `assets/design_<mode>_{auto,confirm,presentation}` files.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:27:- `command-metadata.json`'s `preferSiblingWhen` entries no longer present `/design:design-mcp-open-design` as a runnable sibling command; the transport has none.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:70:The canonical creation surface maps `/interface:{design,foundations,motion,audit,design-reference}` to the stable `interface`, `foundations`, `motion`, `audit`, and `md-generator` modes. All five commands share [`shared/creation-contract.md`](./shared/creation-contract.md). The former `/design:*` alias namespace is retired — `/interface:*` is the sole creation surface.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/manual-testing-playbook.md:3:description: \"Lean manual scenarios for verifying the packet-012 style database (adapter modes, indexer, operator surface) and the /interface:* creation commands + /design:* aliases.\"\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/manual-testing-playbook.md:29:| CMD-03 | `/design:*` aliases resolve to the canonical commands | Backward compatibility preserved | `commands/design/*.md` |\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:288:- Canonical commands: `/interface:design`, `/interface:foundations`, `/interface:motion`, `/interface:audit`, and `/interface:design-reference`. These are the sole public design command surface; the former `/design:*` alias namespace is retired.\n","metadata":{"output":".opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/feature-catalog.md:201:`/interface:{design,foundations,motion,audit,design-reference}` maps to the unchanged `interface`, `foundations`, `motion`, `audit` and `md-generator` mode IDs. All five commands reference one shared nine-stage creation contract. The corresponding `/design:*` commands remain thin compatibility aliases.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:3:description: \"Five canonical /interface:* creation commands, one shared nine-stage contract, and additive /design:* compatibility aliases.\"\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:20:The former `/design:{interface,foundations,motion,audit,md-generator}` commands remain thin compatibility aliases. The aliases are additive and preserve arguments while executing the canonical contracts in place.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:30:Compatibility metadata maps each `/design:*` alias one-to-one to a canonical `/interface:*` command. The alias layer does not create new modes, remove old consumers or change the stable mode roster.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/feature-catalog/creation-command-surface/interface-creation-commands.md:43:| `.opencode/commands/design/*.md` | Compatibility routers | Preserves the five `/design:*` aliases. |\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.6.0.0.md:26:- `/design:interface`, `/design:foundations`, `/design:motion`, `/design:audit` and `/design:md-generator` remain thin compatibility aliases.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:8:> Covers the net cumulative change since v1.2.0.0's mode-local procedure operating model: the five `/design:*` commands moved to a router+assets shape, a sixth transport mode joined the registry, and the first-ever full manual execution of the playbook found and fixed a real routing/authoring-boundary defect for every mode.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:15:- Router+assets command shape for all five `/design:*` commands, mirroring the `speckit`/`create`/`deep` command family pattern: a thin router file plus `assets/design_<mode>_{auto,confirm,presentation}` files.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/changelog/v1.4.3.0.md:27:- `command-metadata.json`'s `preferSiblingWhen` entries no longer present `/design:design-mcp-open-design` as a runnable sibling command; the transport has none.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:70:The canonical creation surface maps `/interface:{design,foundations,motion,audit,design-reference}` to the stable `interface`, `foundations`, `motion`, `audit`, and `md-generator` modes. All five commands share [`shared/creation-contract.md`](./shared/creation-contract.md). The former `/design:*` alias namespace is retired — `/interface:*` is the sole creation surface.\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/manual-testing-playbook.md:3:description: \"Lean manual scenarios for verifying the packet-012 style database (adapter modes, indexer, operator surface) and the /interface:* creation commands + /design:* aliases.\"\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/manual-testing-playbook.md:29:| CMD-03 | `/design:*` aliases resolve to the canonical commands | Backward compatibility preserved | `commands/design/*.md` |\n.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:288:- Canonical commands: `/interface:design`, `/interface:foundations`, `/interface:motion`, `/interface:audit`, and `/interface:design-reference`. These are the sole public design command surface; the former `/design:*` alias namespace is retired.\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && grep -rn \"/design:\\|commands/design\" .opencode/skills/sk-design/ 2>&1 | gre