{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606577315,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82d751df792195660745","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show 9a42aedae4 -- .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/006-retire-design-alias-namespace/implementation-summary.md 2>&1 | head -40"},"output":"commit 9a42aedae498924a5c8f0019a208e015946d941e\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 20:53:08 2026 +0200\n\n    refactor(sk-design): retire the /design:* alias namespace; /interface:* is the sole command surface (012/006)\n    \n    Collapse the sk-design command surface to a single visible namespace.\n    /interface:* (design, design-reference, foundations, motion, audit) becomes\n    the sole primary command surface, and the /design:* compatibility-alias layer\n    is deleted end to end - no alias wrappers, assets, metadata records, router\n    mappings, or checker/test assertions.\n    \n    - Delete commands/design/ (5 alias wrappers + their workflow assets).\n    - Re-key command-metadata.json, hub-router.json, and mode-registry.json onto\n      /interface:* with zero compatibility aliases.\n    - Rewrite design-command-surface-check.mjs + its test + interface-command-\n      contract.test.mjs to the single-namespace contract (aliasCount/canonical\n      plumbing removed; every other structural check preserved).\n    - Reconcile README.md + SKILL.md prose - the aliases no longer \"remain\" /\n      \"still work\"; the sole surviving mentions state the namespace is retired.\n    - Add the 012/006-retire-design-alias-namespace spec packet.\n    \n    Verified: design-command-surface-check.mjs exits 0 (status valid, 5 commands,\n    0 drift); 15/15 surface + contract tests green; commands/desi