{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606680247,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82d8e4277300b9d0f6b6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show dc7fdfb0a7 -- \".opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging/spec.md\" 2>&1 | head -60"},"output":"commit dc7fdfb0a746bc89dc932a71d0a4cdcba8b90a0a\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 13:56:57 2026 +0200\n\n    docs(sk-doc): register phase 012 and bring 020 tree to clean full-depth validation\n    \n    Register 012-code-dir-naming-enforcement as a follow-on phase under the\n    020 hyphen-naming program. It extends the closed 000-011 migration to the\n    one scope that migration never covered: code directories inside skills\n    (leading-underscore and __tests__ dirs the packaging and repo-wide guards\n    never scanned). Adds the Level-2 doc set, registers it in the parent phase\n    map (both tables), and threads 011's successor reference.\n    \n    Registering 012 made the parent validate at full depth, which surfaced\n    pre-existing adjacency and thin-doc debt across the 020 tree, unrelated to\n    012. Closed all of it so every phase-parent passes validate.sh --strict:\n    \n    - PHASE_LINKS: added the missing predecessor/successor cross-references to\n      67 child spec.md files (121 -> 0 gaps across every nesting depth).\n    - SECTION_COUNTS: added one requirement (REQ-005) to 33 thin Level-2 docs,\n      each mirroring that doc's own success-criterion evidence deliverable (no\n      invented scope; 4 -> 5 requirements to meet the Level-2 minimum).\n    - Reconciled generated metadata for every touched folder (re-backfilled\n      graph-metadata.json, refreshed continuity timestamps).\n    \n    Verified: full-depth validate.sh --strict across all 178 folders in the\n    020 tree = 0 errors, 0 warnings. 012 validates clean standalone. Every\n    change is scoped to the 020 packet.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PqyZVWPMuG8aTNsmVnj35K\n\ndiff --git a/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging/spec.md b/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging/spec.md\nindex 1117ea6795..cb4fba1c57 100644\n--- a/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging/spec.md\n+++ b/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging/spec.md\n@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@ parent: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates\n _memory:\n   continuity:\n     packet_pointer: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/003-create-generators-and-templates/001-create-skill-and-packaging\"\n-    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-18T06:41:37.848Z\"\n+    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-20T11:05:55Z\"\n     last_updated_by: \"codex\"\n     recent_action: \"Completed create-skill scaffold and package output naming migration\"\n     next_safe_action: \"No child work remains\"\n@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@ _memory:\n <!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/hvr_rules.md -->\n \n # Feature Specification: Create-skill Scaffolding and Packaging\n+> Phase adjacency — successor `002-catalog-and-playbook-generators`.\n \n > Parallel child under `003-create-generators-and-templates`; sibling ordering is not a runtime dependency.\n \n","metadata":{"output":"commit dc7fdfb0a746bc89dc932a71d0a4cdcba8b90a0a\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon J