{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606713346,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82d9656f71938e48244c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show dc7fdfb0a7 -- \".opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement/spec.md\" 2>&1 | head -60"},"output":"commit dc7fdfb0a746bc89dc932a71d0a4cdcba8b90a0a\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 13:56:57 2026 +0200\n\n    docs(sk-doc): register phase 012 and bring 020 tree to clean full-depth validation\n    \n    Register 012-code-dir-naming-enforcement as a follow-on phase under the\n    020 hyphen-naming program. It extends the closed 000-011 migration to the\n    one scope that migration never covered: code directories inside skills\n    (leading-underscore and __tests__ dirs the packaging and repo-wide guards\n    never scanned). Adds the Level-2 doc set, registers it in the parent phase\n    map (both tables), and threads 011's successor reference.\n    \n    Registering 012 made the parent validate at full depth, which surfaced\n    pre-existing adjacency and thin-doc debt across the 020 tree, unrelated to\n    012. Closed all of it so every phase-parent passes validate.sh --strict:\n    \n    - PHASE_LINKS: added the missing predecessor/successor cross-references to\n      67 child spec.md files (121 -> 0 gaps across every nesting depth).\n    - SECTION_COUNTS: added one requirement (REQ-005) to 33 thin Level-2 docs,\n      each mirroring that doc's own success-criterion evidence deliverable (no\n      invented scope; 4 -> 5 requirements to meet the Level-2 minimum).\n    - Reconciled generated metadata for every touched folder (re-backfilled\n      graph-metadata.json, refreshed continuity timestamps).\n    \n    Verified: full-depth validate.sh --strict across all 178 folders in the\n    020 tree = 0 errors, 0 warnings. 012 validates clean standalone. Every\n    change is scoped to the 020 packet.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PqyZVWPMuG8aTNsmVnj35K\n\ndiff --git a/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement/spec.md b/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement/spec.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000000..3e43885c13\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement/spec.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,164 @@\n+---\n+title: \"Feature Specification: code-directory naming enforcement (020 phase 012)\"\n+description: \"Close the naming gap the 000-011 migration never scoped: leading-underscore and __tests__ code directories inside skills. Extend the canon, broaden enforcement to code dirs, de-duplicate per-mode restatements, and rename the sk-design styles code dirs.\"\n+parent: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention\"\n+trigger_phrases:\n+  - \"code directory naming enforcement\"\n+  - \"leading underscore db engine tests naming\"\n+  - \"naming checker code dirs scope gap\"\n+importance_tier: important\n+contextType: planning\n+_memory:\n+  continuity:\n+    packet_pointer: \"sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement\"\n+    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-20T10:42:52Z\"\n+    last_updated_by: \"spec-author\"\n+    recent_action: \"Author the 012 code-dir naming-enforcement phase spec\"\n+    next_safe_action: \"Plan then build the shared code-dir naming checker and canon extension\"\n+    blockers: []\n+    key_files:\n+      - \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/references/filesystem-naming-convention.md\"\n+      - \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/shared/scripts/check_no_new_snake_case.py\"\n+      - \".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/scripts/package_skill.py\"\n","metadata":{"output":"commit dc7fdfb0a746bc89dc932a71d0a4cdcba8b90a0a\nAuthor: Michel Kerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>\nDate:   Mon Jul 20 13:56:57 2026 +0200\n\n    docs(sk-doc): register phase 012 and bring 020 tree to clean full-depth validation\n    \n    Register 012-code-dir-naming-enforcement as a follow-on phase under the\n    020 hyphen-naming program. It extends the closed 000-011 migration to the\n    one scope that migration never covered: code directories inside skills\n    (leading-underscore and __tests__ dirs the packaging and repo-wide guards\n    never scanned). Adds the Level-2 doc set, registers it in the parent phase\n    map (both tables), and threads 011's successor reference.\n    \n    Registering 012 made the parent validate at full depth, which surfaced\n    pre-existing adjacency and thin-doc debt across the 020 tree, unrelated to\n    012. Closed all of it so every phase-parent passes validate.sh --strict:\n    \n    - PHASE_LINKS: added the missing predecessor/successor cross-references to\n      67 child spec.md files (121 -> 0 gaps across every nesting depth).\n    - SECTION_COUNTS: added one requirement (REQ-005) to 33 thin Level-2 docs,\n      each mirroring that doc's own success-criterion evidence deliverable (no\n      invented scope; 4 -> 5 requirements to meet the Level-2 minimum).\n    - Reconciled generated metadata for every touched folder (re-backfilled\n      graph-metadata.json, refreshed continuity timestamps).\n    \n    Verified: full-depth validate.sh --strict across all 178 folders in the\n    020 tree = 0 errors, 0 warnings. 012 validates clean standalone. Every\n    change is scoped to the 020 packet.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PqyZVWPMuG8aTNsmVnj35K\n\ndiff --git a/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/012-code-dir-naming-enforcement/spec.md b/.opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-h