{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784606794336,"sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_019f82daa1b978139557383d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show dc7fdfb0a7:\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/008-component-migration/005-cli-external-orchestration/004-cli-codex/spec.md\" 2>&1 | sed -n '/^## 4. REQUIREMENTS/,/^## 5\\./p'"},"output":"## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 [P0] | All local authored candidates are mapped | Five reference and two asset source names have unique kebab-case targets; any execution-time candidate is dispositioned before mutation |\n| REQ-002 [P0] | Active local references resolve | `SKILL.md`, README, asset links, and active component documents contain no stale source path |\n| REQ-003 [P0] | Codex contracts are preserved | Availability/self-invocation guards, model/reasoning flags, sandbox modes, review/search/image guidance, and handback semantics match BASE |\n| REQ-004 [P1] | Delegated and exempt surfaces remain separate | Playbook, changelog, identifiers/keys, Python/package names, and tool-mandated filenames are unchanged |\n| REQ-005 [P1] | The map is reversible | Source-target entries are bijective, collision-free, and git-revertable |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n","metadata":{"output":"## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 [P0] | All local authored candidates are mapped | Five reference and two asset source names have unique kebab-case targets; any execution-time candidate is dispositioned before mutation |\n| REQ-002 [P0] | Active local references resolve | `SKILL.md`, README, asset links, and active component documents contain no stale source path |\n| REQ-003 [P0] | Codex contracts are preserved | Availability/self-invocation guards, model/reasoning flags, sandbox modes, review/search/image guidance, and handback semantics match BASE |\n| REQ-004 [P1] | Delegated and exempt surfaces remain separate | Playbook, changelog, identifiers/keys, Python/package names, and tool-mandated filenames are unchanged |\n| REQ-005 [P1] | The map is reversible | Source-target entries are bijective, collision-free, and git-revertable |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0092-deep-review-session-shipped-work && git show dc7fdfb0a7:\".opencode/specs/sk-doc/020-hyphen-naming-convention/008-component-migration/005-cli-external-orchestration/004-cli-codex/spec.md\" 2>&1 | sed -n '/^## 4. REQUIREMENTS/,/^## 5\\./p'","time":{"start":1784606794330,"end":1784606794332}},"id":"prt_f82daa23b001xhh1yOW7hQm5hy","sessionID":"ses_07d2d665dffedyOb0L7GbCTElX","messageID":"msg_f82da947d001MuBNEdjuXgMat5"}}
